description.plain:
“touch tank” is a 2022 single by quinnie. The song went viral on TikTok prior to its release. touch tank is about a man who is gentle in a relationship. quinnie uses various summer motifs to describe her  relationship with the man throughout the song.

quinnie also has donated 100% of the first week of streams to the Indigenous Rising Women Abortion Fund.

annotations: I used to dive deep ’til I got splashed in the face

quinnie is probably talking about a past relationship experience, in which they “dove deep”, meaning committed themselves until they “got splashed in the face”, which is probably a metaphor for getting hurt by the one who they committed themselves to.

Canceled a hot hipster threesome for you
 ’Cause I preach of freedom, but you’re a fucking great excuse
quinnie usually “preaches freedom” of sexuality and non-monogamy, but instead, uses the subject as an excuse to do something unlike them.
So now I can’t suck in my stomach around you anymore

Sucking in a stomach is a form of trying to look ‘skinnier’ and ‘more attractive’ in modern day society. This can lead to not being able to breath properly in some cases. As the writers breath is ‘taken away’ this means they cannot suck In their stomach which they have done to become prettier in their love interests eyes.

Despite being up to 9 m (30 ft) in maximum length and to a disc size of 7 m (23 ft) across with a weight of about 3,000 kg (6,600 lb) Manta Rays are gentle giants! This shows that he is gentle in this relationship.
The clean shirt suggests he’s putting in some effort for his love interest, building the idea of his ‘gentleness’.

annotations: No amount of nail polish could paint you a good man

A man painting his nails is ostensibly a feminist act, since it experiments with gender roles.

However, painted nails has been reduced to a signifier that someone is ‘feminist’, and is usually just done to seem more attractive to girls. It does not indicate any true commitment to feminist ideas.

In this way, the man paints his nails to be manipulative, to trick girls into thinking he will treat them better than other men. This is the ‘soft boy scam’ referenced in the previous lines.

quinnie is specifically commenting on how no amount of acts like this – superficially feminist – could make a difference to this man’s true behaviour.
So fuck all your gold stars, the cherries in the backyard

In her 2019 track “gold star” quinnie sings about gold stars – something used to reward a child’s good behaviour:

Make my bed for you
For when you finally come through
Do I write these sad songs just to sing them to you?
Could you give me a gold star and see me through?

In a TikTok promoting the then-unreleased song, quinnie shared:

Though that song [“gold star”] will always have a place in my heart, time made me view it in a very different light. [“man”] is my response to “gold star.”
